title: Nice Duck Dummy
text:
My dogs are NOT retrievers but they have shown a great love for running out in the water and snatching duck decoys and bringing them back on land so I can place them in the water and we do it all over again. Pretty sure they think it's an amusing and unusual game of fetch. I figured why not try a fake duck actually meant for dogs to grab.

This duck has been a huge hit! The long rope makes it very easy to throw a long distance. It has been fairly durable except for when somebody ran off with it and decided to chew off its bill. Not the manufacturers fault. This is made as a training item, not a chew toy. The missing bill has not affected the throw or fetch quality and no one (except maybe the duck) seems to mind.

This is a good quality fake duck for the price, especially if you have pups you are actually training to retrieve a duck without biting it in half.

title: Far From Expectations
text:
The Organ 7 Chakra necklace is... well, no other way to put it. It is disappointing. It arrived nicely packaged in its own little box with a pull tab. On opening, I was expecting something a bit more finished looking. This looks like a beginner's attempt at making resin "art" with rocks and a squiggle of copper.

The resin is chunky and a little cloudy, the edges were sanded, sure, but not sanded and cleared. Honestly, the rocks inside the resin may be rocks but they look more like little chunks of paper. If one was looking for a necklace for crystal healing purposes, this is not it. Even for an interesting necklace to wear without seeking healing, this still is not it. You could get away with giving this to a 6 year old and they would probably think it's cool as long as they still color outside the lines (their critical eye has not yet developed).

title: Nicely Packaged and Pretty
text:
The HOMHOW triple protection bracelet arrives attractively packaged in a little linen covered box. The bracelet is held and displayed inside in such a way that it is laid out nicely on opening (it is not just floating around loose).

The bracelet itself is very pretty, with polished hematite, tiger's eye, and a blue stone I cannot identify. I am not sure which stone on here is supposed to be obsidian. I did not get this for healing or protective properties so a lack of a type of stone does not bother me. I got it because I like how it looks. To be fair, I DO like that it is heavy enough that I am aware of it on my wrist. If stuck in a conversation I am not enjoying this bracelet gives me something else to think about so maybe it relieves stress in that way.

I like how the size adjusts. It is easy for one person to put on and adjust. There are two ties on the underside --I call it the underside as it is where the adjustment is and it neatly stays put on the underside of my wrist -- which pull in opposite directions to make the bracelet smaller. As these ties get longer, the bracelet gets smaller. Cool! They do not loosen over the course of the day wearing it so the bracelet does stay at whatever size you adjust it to be.

I got this for myself, but this would also make a great gift.

text:
I LOVE this water bottle! I bought it as a gift for my mother to announce my wife being pregnant with our second kid.

I looked around at a lot of places locally but none could engrave the name like this. I didn't want something like a sticker or paint that would wear off, I wanted it to be permanent.

I also looked around at other places online and were a little cheaper but wait times were multiple weeks. The seller was AMAZING! I received the water bottle a day before Amazon said it would arrive and I received within only 3 days of ordering it which is amazing!

The bottle has worked just as well as big name brands of keeping water cold. Haven't tried hot since it was a gift and just wanted to test how well cold drinks worked.

The seller sent me a picture of what the name would like prior to engraving, so there was no worrying about what would arrive. Upon arrival it looked exactly as advertised and we want to order more now!

While the price is a little expensive for a standard water bottle, it's still cheaper than some big name companies yet isn't personalized so you can't beat the deal!

Would highly recommend both the water bottle and seller and will absolutely Ben ordering more items in the future!

As my hair is very thin and fine I need to "tighten" the clip by spreading the clip out along the stick (make the holes as far apart as possible) and it holds all day but these are more than big enough to work for thick hair.. The tool work is beautiful, I'm almost disappointed that I have to wear it on the back of my head so can't see it all day.

This came today and I was so excited to get it in my hot little hands. I just started Bullet Journaling and wanted something bigger than the norm. The fit with the single journal is snug so I worried it wouldn't be able to accommodate two but it does so quite nicely with the help of a couple of DIY elastics. The leather is soft and smooth to the touch. There are a few minor marks but I'm probably going to put more marks on it as I use it so that doesn't bother me at all.
